It's a failing of many type systems of older languages (except Pascal).The best way in many languages for flags is using unsigned integers that are botwise-ORed together.In pseudocode:    Object someObject;
    foo (someObject, Object.Flag1 | Object.Flag2 | Object.Flag3);

Whatever language you are using, it probably has some namespaced way to define flags as `(1 << 0)` and `(1 << 1)` etc.
